I would say as a gamer in general there are many reasons for giving up the game entirely, but I couldn’t honestly answer your question as to why a bard would re-roll his/her class other than maybe twisting.<br>
<br>
Personally, I was never satisfied with having one designated function in a group such as healing, tanking, or straight DPS so a bard offered me the variety I craved.<br>
<br>
However, I can understand how people can grow tired of the constant attention bards require and how we can often times miss out on things while twisting such as chatting and other social interaction which is a big part of what makes EQ.<br>
Add in the physical aspect of twisting and you have a recipe for failure. I can remember 15+ hour stretches of AA grinding finished with an icepack on my hand to relieve the pain.<br>
<br>
I unofficially left EQ a couple of months ago, but I can honestly say that if I end up returning I wouldn’t play any class other than my bard.<br>
<br>
As for my leaving the game: I think if I could contribute it to one thing it would be lack of interest and from that grew feelings of obligation to everyones enjoyment but my own. In short, it became more of a chore than fun and I had to step back for awhile<br>
<br>
Jordell Da’ Maestro<br>
Morell Thule<br>
